snippet.textDisplay:
Here's my interpretation. The Tree is a neutral entity/diety, which connects to all life through language, but the tree is also protected by angels (white feathery outfit). One day, the sun doesn't appear. Jiu being the leader of the angels and lead observer (we see her directly in the tree of language), sees the bloody nature of the hate language, which caused her to close her eyes. The second Angel (Yoohyeon), asks the question "Tell me why, I don't lie", which signifies their innocence.

As the MV unfolds, you start to see their innocence wither away, represented by a smaller white child figure disintegrating in front of a single black adult figure (Sua). This dark figure is at the world tree (sword at the ready) to attack with hate. Gahyeon and Dami's sees the evil coming and tries to fix the problem, but whatever they do fails. Sua continues to spread the evil to the point the angels snaps (breaking of the crystal, explosion from the tree) and falls into a crazed mental state. Siyeon sings as they wake up, their innocence is gone, they have killed all sense of their pain and fallen into a state of denial. They've even become the angel of death. Their white outfits are now black. They leave the Tree of Language in darkness into the dystopian world. To be Continued...

Loads of people call Dreamcatcher underrated but they’re gradually getting more recognition at this moment so I don’t think underrated is the right word we should use, but instead, under-appreciated.

These girls easily have a flawless discography, amazing stage presence, beautiful but mysterious music videos like no other, a distinct sound compared to other groups, great dance, vocal and rap skills and are basically full of powerful visuals. If you see big groups, this is literally what fandoms always look at, but it’s as if noone can see that Dreamcatcher has it too, and maybe even better.

To help them succeed and make them an even stabler group, we should vote to get their first win, stream not only this music video but the others and performances, and keep spreading news about them on social media!

snippet.textDisplay:
The horn thing they are doing with their hand actually symbolises a very great meaning.. In Buddhism open palm refers to protection.. First they are showing an open palm towards themselves that is earlier when they were weak and afraid of demons and evil things (aka haters) they were protecting themselves.. Then secondly they are doing an open palm towards the audience that means they are no more afraid of demons (aka haters) then they are doing the horn thing which in Indian culture symbolises lion.. and in Buddhism symbolises expulsion of demons and bad things.. So they are symbolising that they are no more afraid and have become strong as lions and are ready for the destruction of demons (..aka again haters)..
I am not sure.. this is just my theory..
Btw don't forget to stream their mv and comeback stages..
